# minio CVE-2025-59952
# XML tag value substitution in minio-java 8.5.10.
# Fix is 8.6.0, but that version removed OkHttp from compile scope,
# breaking MinioConfig compilation without adding okhttp as explicit dependency.
# Risk is low: requires attacker to control S3 server XML responses.
# Re-evaluate when a minio version fixes both issues simultaneously.
CVE-2025-59952

# jackson-core GHSA-72hv-8253-57qq
# DoS via Number Length Constraint Bypass in Async Parser.
# Current version 2.19.0 has no patch in the 2.19.x branch.
# Fix exists in 2.18.6 (older branch) and 2.21.1 (not yet released).
# Downgrading to 2.18.x would break Spring Boot 3.5.0 compatibility.
# Accept risk: internal service, not directly exposed to untrusted input streams.
# Re-evaluate when Spring Boot 3.5.x ships with a patched jackson-core 2.19.x.
GHSA-72hv-8253-57qq
